     \"reason\": \"node_cpu_usage_rate increase from 17.08% to 23.66% (32% increase) suggesting resource pressure\",\n      \"evidence\": \"node_cpu_usage_rate: 17.08→23.66 (32%↑)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-05\",\n      \"reason\": \"node_cpu_usage_rate increase from 18.1% to 23.9% (28% increase) indicating system-wide resource contention\",\n      \"evidence\": \"node_cpu_usage_rate: 18.1→23.9 (28%↑)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Analysis Summary:**\n\nThe primary issue appears to be centered around the **adservice** component, with all three pods (adservice-0, adservice-1, adservice-2) experiencing significant CPU usage spikes and response time degradation. The most severely affected is **adservice-0**, showing a 193% increase in CPU usage and 142% increase in response time.\n\nThe node-level metrics show moderate CPU usage increases on nodes aiops-k8s-07 and aiops-k8s-05, which likely contributed to the overall system degradation but appear to be secondary effects rather than the root cause.\n\nThe pattern suggests a **service-level performance issue** with the adservice component, possibly due to increased load, resource contention, or application-level problems affecting all its pods simultaneously."}
